The death toll in the floods in South Africa's KwaZulu-Natal has climbed to 59, according to the local government. South African President Cyril Ramaphosa will visit the flood-hit areas of KwaZulu-Natal on Wednesday to offer support to affected communities and assess the response of government and civil society to this critical situation. (Cover: Heavy rain causes flooding in Pinetown, near Durban, South Africa, April 12, 2022. /CFP)